	The terms presented here are applied either to all the space surrounding the barn and the stables or to a smaller area exclusive of the pens for the farm stock.  In the narrower sense these terms denote the space between the dwelling and the barn, fenced or unfenced, the place `in front of the barn' where wagons and other farm implements are often kept.
	The terms are: "barnyard", "farm" "yard", "lot" ("the" "lot"), "barn" "lot", "stable" "lot".  "Pound", given on the preceding map, often means "barnyard".
	For specific definitions see the commentary of the preceding map.
